                <summary>Margaret Shayer left a fund for children in Staunton, selected the late
                    Samuel Clarke, Esq., as trustee. By the time of Clarke's death, the fund was
                    close to $4,000. In the absence of an heir, Clarke's administrator, John N.
                    Hendren, Esq., asked circuit court to appoint a new trustee. Judge Thompson
                    declared the fund void and the possession of the commonwealth. Following a
                    petition from residents of Staunton, however, the legislature authorize the
                    court to dispose of the sum. The court decided to distribute the money among the
                    various male and female academies. J.B. Baldwin, Geo. Baylor, and A.D. Trotter
                    were chosen to select pupils who would receive assistance from the
                fund.</summary>
            </div>
